main event: An unidentified flying object was observed near Sioux Narrows, Ontario, Canada on August 25, 1960 and August 29, 1960.
interesting points: The object was observed by ground-based radar on August 25, 1960 and was described as being as mobile as a conventional aircraft, disappearing behind trees.
The observers did not report the sighting until September 13, 1960, so the report was considered to have insufficient data.
On August 29, 1960, a visual sighting was reported of a bright, aluminum-colored object that descended behind trees after being observed for about 90-100 seconds.
NASA forwarded the August 29, 1960 sighting report to the Air Force for further investigation.
The reports indicate the object was observed both visually and on radar, but no photographs were taken.
